# Analyst Visual - KX Dashboards

Original URL: https://code.kx.com/dashboards/analystvisual/

# Analyst Visual

A container for a [Grammar-of-
Graphics](https://www.cs.uic.edu/~wilkinson/TheGrammarOfGraphics/GOG.html)
visualization.

![Screenshot](../img/analyst/analystvisuals.jpg)

## Basics

![Screenshot](../img/analyst/analystbasics.png)

_Name_

    A name for the component provided by the user. 
_Data Source_

    Grammar-of-Graphics written in the editor [connecting](../datasources/#connections) to KX Analyst; see [setup](./#setup) for an example.  [Data source](../datasources/)
_Selected Value_

     [View State Parameters](../viewstateparameters/)

## Style, Format, Margins

[Style](../style/#component-style) for common style settings

## Setup

Step 1. Create a [connection](../datasources/#connections) to Analyst in
Dashboards.

![Screenshot](../img/analyst/analystworkspacecomplete.jpg)

![Screenshot](../img/analyst/analystconnectiondashboards.jpg)

Step 2. Create a new [data source](../datasources/) in KX Dashboards using the
Analyst connection; a simple Grammar of Graphics example:

![Screenshot](../img/analyst/analystdashdatasource.jpg)

    
    
    .gg.dash.go 
    .qp.theme[.gg.dash.dark] 
    .qp.point[([]x:til 45); `x; `x; ::]
    

![Screenshot](../img/analyst/analystoutput.jpg)

